data.title: Antonie Alexandrová Svoboda (1847
data.meta_description: Her father was František Alexandr and her mother was Antonia Malek. After her husband's death, Antonia decided to move to Arkansas in 1900.  Her four youngest children went with her.  They returned to Nebraska in 1904 or 1905, purchasing the Riely farm northwest of Lawrence, Nebraska.  She and the boys worked the farm,...
